      "content": "Let's say I'm a new developer in the Mina ecosystem. I'm used to writing loops. But, suddenly, everyone keeps telling me that I should use o1js's recursion pattern instead because it's faster and better for the network.\n\nWhy should I care? Is it just because generating a proof takes longer time? Surely, if I can generate the proof, the network will accept it, regardless?",
